It was three in the morning. There's probably mistakes everywhere.

Written by Rory Harman

Black

In the darkness, we hear a thudding noise, and some muffled swearing.

INT. Will's appt. - Morning

Establishing shot focuses on Will's face, as his eyes open.

He is laying in bed. He mouths words the words " What the fuck?"

His calendar says its saturday. He groins as he pulls himself out of his bed. He's wearing socks, boxers and a t-shirt on, and his hear is matted and sticking out in different directions. He shuffles towards where the sound is coming from. He stops in the center of the LIVING ROOM.

Will

Holy shit.

On Will's couch is his friend Charlie who is calmly sipping coffee, and reading a book off of the coffee table. He sees Will and grins sheepishly. Next to him is a dead body, with a large wound in it's head.

Will (cont'd)

WHAT THE FUCK IS THAT?!

Charlie

It's a body.. Duh.

Will

I CAN FUCKING TELL WHAT IT IS.

WHAT THE FUCK IS A DEAD

BODY DOING ON MY FUCKING COUCH?!

Charlie

***** Dude. I had to put him somewhere.

It woulda looked weird if I just.. you know...

left him where he was...

Will

WELL WHY THE FUCK IS HE ON

MY FUCKING COUCH?

Charlie

Dude, relax i-

Will

I CAN'T RELAX. THERE'S A

DEAD BODY ON MY COUCH. WHY IS THERE A

DEAD BODY ON MY COUCH?

Charlie

Dude, I told you already.

I had to put him somewhere.

OBVIOUSLY, I couldn't just leave him

where he was after I stabbed him in

the face.

Will

WHY DID YOU STAB HIM IN THE FACE?

Charlie

I... Didn't like him...

Will

WELL WHY THE FUCK DID YOU BRING HIM HERE?

Why couldn't you have taken him ANYWHERE else?

Charlie

I don't know dude. It was kinda..

you know... spur of the moment.

Besides, you're... you know... the safe one.

Will

What do you mean "the safe one"?

Charlie

You know... The safe one...

Out of everyone I know,

You're probably the guy least likely

to get in any kind of trouble.

It seemed like a good

idea at the time.

Will

WELL THAT'S NO GOOD REASON TO BRING

HIM HERE. SPEAKING OF WHICH, GET HIM

OFF OF MY COUCH NOW. THERE'S BLOOD

GOING EVERYWHERE

Charlie

Dude! I put down newspaper.

Will

Yeah. Like ONE under his head.

Charlie

Well THAT's where the bleeding was

coming from. I thought it made sense

to put something THERE.

Will

Well that's great BUT YOU PUT HIM

SITTING UPRIGHT ON MY COUCH.

SPEAKING OF WHICH, GET HIM OFF MY

COUCH NOW!

Charlie.

Why are you yelling at me like this

is MY fault all of a sudden?

Will

IT IS YOUR FUCKING FAULT?!

Charlie

What do you mean?

Will

YOU'RE THE ONE WHO FUCKING STABBED

HIM IN THE FACE.

Charlie

Dude! He was asking for it.

Will

Oh yeah? How so?

Charlie looks up momentarily.

CUT TO - EXT. A movie theater. Nighttime.

Charlie is standing in a line of people.

suddenly, a man cuts in front of him.

Charlie

Hey, asshole. Don't cut in front of me.

Harry

What are you you going to do about it?

Stab me in the face?

Charlie

Yeah. I could.

Harry

Yeah.. I bet you could.

So what, you gonna do it or

what?

Charlie

Yeah!

Harry.

Yeah?

Charlie

YEAH?

Harry

YEAH?

Cut to caption: TEN MINUTES LATER.

Harry

COME ON MAN!

Charlie

Alright!

Charlie pulls out a knife and begins to swing towards

Harry.

CUT TO INT. Will's Appt. Still morning.

Will is speechless.

The DOORBELL rings.

Will

SHIT!

Ok. Charlie, we have to get this

body out of here RIGHT NOW

Charlie

Right! What're we going to do?

Will

I DON'T KNOW! He's YOURS.

Voice from outside

Hello? I can hear voices in

there.

Charlie

Just a moment.

Will

Don't say that. It'll only

encourage them.

Ok. I have a sleeping bag

in my closet.

Charlie

Right!

Charlie leaves the room to go find Will's sleeping bag.

The Doorbell rings again.

Voice

HELLO?!

Will

HOLD ON.

Charlie enters the room again, with the rolled up SLEEPING BAG

which he takes the elastic band off of, and unrolls with a

big sweep, by holding the end and throwing it away from him.

Charlie

Yeah... Er... we're naked.

Together.

The two begin to bag the body.

Will

Don't say THAT.

Charlie

Why not? It's not like it really

matters at this point, dude.

Will

The walls in this place are paper

thin. My neighbors probably heard

you.

Charlie

Well then dude, they probably heard

you yelling about there being a

corpse on your couch.

Besides, I thought you WERE gay

so it's really probably nothing new

to them.

Will opens his mouth to protest.

The two have, by this point, finished bagging Harry's corpse.

Charlie (cont'd)

Alright dude, let's go ahead and get

this guy out of here.

The doorbell rings frantically.

CUT TO - EXT. Will's Appt.

A small girl in a girl scout uniform is standing on Will's

doormat. She looks expectant.

She waits.

CUT TO - INT. Will's Appt. Still Morning.

Charlie and Will are struggling to move the corpse in the sleeping bag.

Charlie (mouthing)

How are we going to get this thing

out of here?

CUT TO - EXT. Will's Appt.

The girl scout looks frustrated.

Girl Scout

FUCK YOU BOTH. I'M LEAVING!

She storms off.

CUT TO - Int. Will's Appt.

Charlie

Oh. That solves that.

The following is a montage of footage of Charlie and Will, as they struggle to get the body out of Will's apartment, down the stairs

and into Charlie's car.

It's incomplete.

I'm still way ahead.


Valentine's day is coming up, and that's something that I've been dreading a long time.
It's not that I resent the holiday it's self. It's not that I'm part of the camp of trendy cynics who constantly rail against it because it's cool to hate it, and who claim that it's a ugly and tacky exploitation of sappy emotions. It's not that I'm secretly bitter because the holiday reminds me that I'm alone because of having been too afraid to take an opportunity while I had it, and now, having lost my chance, I'm a hollow, mean-spirited man who enjoys taking the fun out of other people's lives, because I can't get over how empty mine feels. It's those fucking heart candies.
Every year I end up with dozens of them. And I end up falling victim to the same mistake over and over again. Every time I get one, I fill up with the hope that maybe, just maybe, this time it won't taste terrible, and I eat it, and remember that I hate them, only to end up back at the beginning of the cycle moments later, ending only when I'm fully out of them. And then I forget again how much I hate them and wish I had more.
So how the hell did we end up with this junk? There doesn't actually seem to be any clear explanation. No one else seems to like them either.
I like to imagine that it was something like this:
The first candy heart came to be millions of years ago. An early, Neanderthalic, man was seriously injured in the heart during a hunt, and died. The rest of the tribe wanted to bury him, except for one. This visionary thought that maybe he could rescue his fallen companion. So he carved a new heart for the dead man out of bones, and tried to stuff it into the corpse. It didn't work though, so eventually he gave up on trying, and ate the bone heart, unaware that he was making history by in one move inviting the single most wretched candy ever invented*  and performing the first open heart surgery. 

*with the possible exception Spunk, a Danish candy that's supposed to tastes like licorice and salt water; I tried it once and was left with the feeling that I was tasting  death, and made me feel as though there was absolutely no light in the world, and that my soul was being crushed. I think people only buy for the double entendres
Will color and tool around with it a bit more later.

.. When this was published originally, I ended up having to try to explain it to more people than I heard say they liked it. Commentary: The thing is that it doesn't have a definite punch-line. The whole thing is a commentary on different aspects of the film. The initial trap it's self represents the absurdity of the whole film, in that people are constantly shoved into ridiculous and outlandish circumstances. The thought and problem solving process represents how extremely melodramatic and ridiculous the execution is, as well as the irrationality displayed at an alarming constant through the film. The visual style of the comic it's self also works into the commentary, speaking to how the film is visually and and in terms of plot, bland and derisive; trying too hard to emulate other sources in terms of execution and visual style. That every aspect of the ploy is reminiscent of another, better film, and that it seems to be trying very much so to actually look like a film directed by David Fincher.

So, I was playing with a digitial airbrush type thing and I made this : Somewhat amusing, but it needed a background, so I asked around a bit and this is what came of it:

I painted these, along with a few others, on unfolded paper bags, because I'd decided that I needed something to go on my ceiling ( which is why the monster says what it says). After I made them and stuck them up, I decided that they'd look better on my wall, and put a large cloth on my ceiling instead. In actuality, they're between 17x24 inches and 21x28 inches. They aren't terribly refined, I was just doing quick bursts of whatever popped into my head.

Hey hey. It's the back five cards. I really consider a lot of these to be cop-outs. Enjoy.
Well this one is new. I was really trying to get this one into the paper, to see if I somehow could. Apparently the principal is a neo-con. I never finished this one, since I couldn't think of anything funny enough to go with it. If you like it, or have something funny to add, print it out and write your own message. Yeah I totally did this one last year. The fonts and the spacing both seem a bit off to me. Not only did I do this one last year, but this is actually the exact same picture. See above. It's worth noting that I simplified it a lot

To match what I did last year, I'm putting together some valentines cards for this year. In case I don't get everything done completely by then, here are some still somewhat rough versions of some of the cards for this year. I should have everything tied up and put in order by some time tomorrow morning (I'm writing this from the perspective of still seeing it as Sunday night, and not Monday morning.) This is the majority of them. Actually, most of the remainders are some the more light hearted cards of the set. Anyway
This one is going into the school paper's special Valentines issue. I got commissioned to do some of these in a format that could be used for the paper. This one was two. A slightly different version of the graphic was used tho, and the joke ended up being simplified some way or another. I was surprised that this one got used. I did this mainly a throwback to the set I did last year. As was this one. This is pretty much what I had wanted the one from last year's set to look like, and what it didn't end up looking like. Again, I'm just recycling stuff at this point. Oh hi dad. There was a bit of discussion I had with my friend Rafi over whether or not this joke could have been justified doing last year, with that set of cards, since I see it simply as being a more extreme version of the cutter joke. He insisted that it could be worked in. Regardless of how original it is, I still like it, for it's shock value. My journalism teacher called it "the single most repulsive image she'd ever seen"
Tomorrow some time, I'll get everything else together, and put up more printer friendly sheets, for printing out and distributing these to people that you love or hate.

SCIENCE! .... the kid doesn't actually have anything under his mic:gonk: THE FISH OF SCIENCE The high school I go to is cold and depressing and decrepit. Um.... I fell down these stairs and snapped my ankle. This is a high school and these are the Men's room bathroom signs. The freshmen class for some reason thought that it was a good idea to cover a Christmas tree with garbage from fast food places. ...It's a funny and unintentional celebration of consumerism! My English Teacher's lamp. My English teacher also has this thing for collecting candels. The rest of the class was watching some movie, and since I wasn't I took pictures of things. It's a mouse! Like now. Yeah. It's a tongue in a jar. It's on my desk. It smells really funky whenever I take it out. I didn't actually take this picture but it was on the camera. That lamp is on the ceiling?!! Yeah. Christmas lights on low shudderspeed with a shakey camera. AMAZING AND ORIGINAL.

The first from my attempt to remake and expand upon the Valentines cards I did last year. This time around tho, I'm actually doing them all by hand, instead of doing computer traced vector art. And technically all of this batch tho are just rehashes of exact items from the first series. This is actually the third take of the card idea. This particular concept was actually the first I did, and the one that inspired me to actually do the first set. The first time I did it, it was just this by it's self. There was no series of other cards surrounding it. Second rehash. Probably the most mean spirited of any of the cards that I've done so far. It's surprisingly popular with former cutters. Surprisingly popular in general, actually. ... I really hope that people realize that it's intended to be a joke. ... Yes, I do actually feel a little bad about this one. This is actually, for all intents and purposes, even tho it wasn't actually in the set, this particular card is a rehash, even tho it never actually appeared in the first series. My original qualm was that it was too similar as a gag to the "Cut's it" card, but people have insisted to me that there is enough of a difference to merit making it. I did this mostly to humor them. This is really only a mockup, and probably not the finalized image. The final product will probably be much more consistent with the rest, and equally stylized, and with a higher level of realism to it.

My intent with this piece was ( and still is) to send it to this fine gentlemen as a return for the lovely card which I received from him. I'm posting it here in case it gets lost.... That and the fact that it will probably get crumpled.

A few things I found while rummaging through a box of old sketches. Just a somewhat cute doodle of a bear I did really early this year. A character sketch from a very short-lived D&D campaign. I think initially it was supposed to be a bit more masculine of a face. The rest just kinda happened. I really liked the way it turned out, regardless. ... I'll add more later.
